headline: Netflix Lifted Guidance. Is the Stock a Buy Following Its Drop?
summary: Netflix turned in strong results and upbeat guidance.  Netflix (NASDAQ: NFLX) once again delivered strong revenue and earnings growth when it reported its Q2 results on July 17, but the stock nonetheless fell on the news.  As such, expectations were high going into the report.

headline: Can Netflix Stock Double by 2028?
summary: Netflix delivered another impressive quarter, but the stock still fell.  The company is executing across the board.  Investors may not think of Netflix (NASDAQ: NFLX) as the hot growth stock it was a decade ago, but the stock has been on a warpath over the last few years, despite the broader perception that it's a mature company.
